File: Ivan Pillay, Johann van Loggerenberg and Andries Janse van Rensburg were implicated in the so-called rogue unit saga. JOHANNESBURG - Criminal charges against three former senior SARS officials have been officially withdrawn. Ivan Pillay, Johann van Loggerenberg and Andries Janse van Rensburg were implicated in the so-called rogue unit saga. READ: NDPP drops charges against three former SARS officials The NPA announced the decision earlier this month and their brief appearance in the High Court in Pretoria on Monday sealed the deal. In a statement, the three men's lawyers' say no evidence existed about the unit.